{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gn8UifdNGQdCHVnSny7P2D","type":"tool_result","content":"250\t- Shape: normal finding record with `code`, `stage`, `locator`, `doc_anchor`,\n251\t  `detail`\n252\t- Non-surface: not an `Engine.open` `CorruptionKind`, not an `OpenStage`, and\n253\t  not evidence of any open-time integrity knob\n254\t\n255\t### Recovery hint anchors\n256\t\n257\tThe open-path `RecoveryHint.doc_anchor` values cited from `design/errors.md`\n258\tresolve into the recovery workflow headings below.\n259\t\n260\t#### Wal replay failures\n261\t\n262\tCode: `E_CORRUPT_WAL_REPLAY`\n263\t\n264\tOperator path: `fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss --truncate-wal`\n265\t\n266\t#### Header malformed\n267\t\n268\tCode: `E_CORRUPT_HEADER`\n269\t\n270\tOperator path: `fathomdb doctor safe-export <out>` followed by external rebuild\n271\tor re-import.\n272\t\n273\t#### Schema inconsistent\n274\t\n275\tCode: `E_CORRUPT_SCHEMA`\n276\t\n277\tOperator path: investigate with `doctor` and, where applicable, use\n278\t`fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss --rebuild-projections`.\n279\t\n280\t#### Embedder identity drift\n281\t\n282\tCode: `E_CORRUPT_EMBEDDER_IDENTITY`\n283\t\n284\tOperator path: treat as corrupt stored profile state; do not auto-accept an\n285\tidentity change through `Engine.open`.\n286\t\n287\t### Code-to-operator-action cross-reference\n288\t\n289\t| `RecoveryHint.code`           | Canonical owner of typed payload     | Operator path owner                         |\n290\t| ----------------------------- | ------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------- |\n291\t| `E_CORRUPT_WAL_REPLAY`        | `design/errors.md`                   | this file, `#wal-replay-failures`           |\n292\t| `E_CORRUPT_HEADER`            | `design/errors.md`                   | this file, `#header-malformed`              |\n293\t| `E_CORRUPT_SCHEMA`            | `design/errors.md`                   | this file, `#schema-inconsistent`           |\n294\t| `E_CORRUPT_EMBEDDER_IDENTITY` | `design/errors.md`                   | this file, `#embedder-identity-drift`       |\n295\t| `E_CORRUPT_INTEGRITY_CHECK`   | doctor-only report code in this file | this file, `#integrity-check-full-findings` |\n296\t\n297\t## Relationship to runtime SDK\n298\t\n299\tRecovery and doctor tooling are unreachable from the runtime SDK. Python,\n300\tTypeScript, and the Rust facade do not expose SDK equivalents for any\n301\t`doctor` verb (`check-integrity`, `safe-export`, `verify-embedder`, `trace`,\n302\t`dump-schema`, `dump-row-counts`, `dump-profile`) or any `recover` sub-flag.\n303\t\n304\tNo SDK verb mutates a corruption-marked database. The only mutating recovery\n305\tpath is `fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss`.\n306\t\n307\t## Projection repair workflow\n308\t\n309\tProjection failure handling crosses runtime and operator surfaces:"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6045b345-74e5-4485-9471-2a1561990851","uuid":"5acc1cfa-9906-432d-8d91-b91638818327","timestamp":"2026-05-15T23:42:02.243Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-10b-A-low-risk-seams-20260515T234104Z/dev/design/recovery.md","content":"- Shape: normal finding record with `code`, `stage`, `locator`, `doc_anchor`,\n  `detail`\n- Non-surface: not an `Engine.open` `CorruptionKind`, not an `OpenStage`, and\n  not evidence of any open-time integrity knob\n\n### Recovery hint anchors\n\nThe open-path `RecoveryHint.doc_anchor` values cited from `design/errors.md`\nresolve into the recovery workflow headings below.\n\n#### Wal replay failures\n\nCode: `E_CORRUPT_WAL_REPLAY`\n\nOperator path: `fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss --truncate-wal`\n\n#### Header malformed\n\nCode: `E_CORRUPT_HEADER`\n\nOperator path: `fathomdb doctor safe-export <out>` followed by external rebuild\nor re-import.\n\n#### Schema inconsistent\n\nCode: `E_CORRUPT_SCHEMA`\n\nOperator path: investigate with `doctor` and, where applicable, use\n`fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss --rebuild-projections`.\n\n#### Embedder identity drift\n\nCode: `E_CORRUPT_EMBEDDER_IDENTITY`\n\nOperator path: treat as corrupt stored profile state; do not auto-accept an\nidentity change through `Engine.open`.\n\n### Code-to-operator-action cross-reference\n\n| `RecoveryHint.code`           | Canonical owner of typed payload     | Operator path owner                         |\n| ----------------------------- | ------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------- |\n| `E_CORRUPT_WAL_REPLAY`        | `design/errors.md`                   | this file, `#wal-replay-failures`           |\n| `E_CORRUPT_HEADER`            | `design/errors.md`                   | this file, `#header-malformed`              |\n| `E_CORRUPT_SCHEMA`            | `design/errors.md`                   | this file, `#schema-inconsistent`           |\n| `E_CORRUPT_EMBEDDER_IDENTITY` | `design/errors.md`                   | this file, `#embedder-identity-drift`       |\n| `E_CORRUPT_INTEGRITY_CHECK`   | doctor-only report code in this file | this file, `#integrity-check-full-findings` |\n\n## Relationship to runtime SDK\n\nRecovery and doctor tooling are unreachable from the runtime SDK. Python,\nTypeScript, and the Rust facade do not expose SDK equivalents for any\n`doctor` verb (`check-integrity`, `safe-export`, `verify-embedder`, `trace`,\n`dump-schema`, `dump-row-counts`, `dump-profile`) or any `recover` sub-flag.\n\nNo SDK verb mutates a corruption-marked database. The only mutating recovery\npath is `fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss`.\n\n## Projection repair workflow\n\nProjection failure handling crosses runtime and operator surfaces:","numLines":60,"startLine":250,"totalLines":320}}}
