{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ekt9jHkZwq11eQxxJHT5cB","type":"tool_result","content":"80\t- `EngineError`\n81\t\n82\tCanonical leaf mapping lives in `design/errors.md`. This file adopts those\n83\ttypes without renaming them.\n84\t\n85\t## Recovery / operator seam re-exports\n86\t\n87\tThe `fathomdb` facade re-exports the following recovery and reporting types\n88\tfrom `fathomdb-engine` so that `fathomdb-cli` (the only public consumer of\n89\tthese types) compiles against the public Rust surface, not engine internals.\n90\tThese are CLI-only ergonomic types; they are NOT exposed as runtime SDK\n91\tverbs (recovery remains CLI-only — see Non-presence below).\n92\t\n93\tRe-exported types (canonical spellings, locked 2026-05-12):\n94\t\n95\t- `CheckIntegrityOpts`\n96\t- `IntegrityReport`\n97\t- `SafeExportArtifact`\n98\t- `TraceReport`\n99\t- `TraceEvent`\n100\t- `RebuildReport`\n101\t- `RebuildKind`\n102\t- `ExciseReport`\n103\t\n104\tEngine methods backing these types are owned by `design/recovery.md` and\n105\tlisted in `dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md` (Phase 10a). Additional\n106\trecovery seam types added by Phase 10b (e.g. `VerifyEmbedderReport`,\n107\t`DumpSchemaReport`, `DumpRowCountsReport`, `DumpProfileReport`,\n108\t`TruncateWalReport`, `PurgeLogicalIdReport`, `RestoreLogicalIdReport`) land\n109\there as the corresponding engine seams are implemented, per the same\n110\tre-export rule.\n111\t\n112\t## Non-presence\n113\t\n114\tThe Rust runtime surface does not expose recovery verbs. Recovery remains CLI\n115\tonly per `design/recovery.md` and `design/bindings.md`. The re-exported\n116\trecovery types above are present as compile-time symbols for `fathomdb-cli`;\n117\tthe runtime `Engine` does NOT gain corresponding SDK methods.\n118\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6045b345-74e5-4485-9471-2a1561990851","uuid":"b9965fa6-cb32-4355-a391-ca92f596e9d7","timestamp":"2026-05-15T23:42:05.153Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-10b-A-low-risk-seams-20260515T234104Z/dev/interfaces/rust.md","content":"- `EngineError`\n\nCanonical leaf mapping lives in `design/errors.md`. This file adopts those\ntypes without renaming them.\n\n## Recovery / operator seam re-exports\n\nThe `fathomdb` facade re-exports the following recovery and reporting types\nfrom `fathomdb-engine` so that `fathomdb-cli` (the only public consumer of\nthese types) compiles against the public Rust surface, not engine internals.\nThese are CLI-only ergonomic types; they are NOT exposed as runtime SDK\nverbs (recovery remains CLI-only — see Non-presence below).\n\nRe-exported types (canonical spellings, locked 2026-05-12):\n\n- `CheckIntegrityOpts`\n- `IntegrityReport`\n- `SafeExportArtifact`\n- `TraceReport`\n- `TraceEvent`\n- `RebuildReport`\n- `RebuildKind`\n- `ExciseReport`\n\nEngine methods backing these types are owned by `design/recovery.md` and\nlisted in `dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md` (Phase 10a). Additional\nrecovery seam types added by Phase 10b (e.g. `VerifyEmbedderReport`,\n`DumpSchemaReport`, `DumpRowCountsReport`, `DumpProfileReport`,\n`TruncateWalReport`, `PurgeLogicalIdReport`, `RestoreLogicalIdReport`) land\nhere as the corresponding engine seams are implemented, per the same\nre-export rule.\n\n## Non-presence\n\nThe Rust runtime surface does not expose recovery verbs. Recovery remains CLI\nonly per `design/recovery.md` and `design/bindings.md`. The re-exported\nrecovery types above are present as compile-time symbols for `fathomdb-cli`;\nthe runtime `Engine` does NOT gain corresponding SDK methods.\n","numLines":39,"startLine":80,"totalLines":118}}}
