{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HHo34k4wcRgdCpnb5tfBRJ","type":"tool_result","content":"40\t| `64` | recovery completed only because lossy action was explicitly accepted | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n41\t| `65` | doctor/verification surface found actionable non-clean state         | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n42\t| `66` | export/materialization failure on an artifact-producing doctor verb  | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n43\t| `70` | unrecoverable command failure                                        | this file                        |\n44\t| `71` | lock-held or equivalent precondition-blocked outcome                 | this file + `design/bindings.md` |\n45\t\n46\t## Doctor verbs\n47\t\n48\t| Verb              | Synopsis                                                                       | Exit class                          |\n49\t| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------- |\n50\t| `check-integrity` | `fathomdb doctor check-integrity [--quick] [--full] [--round-trip] [--pretty]` | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65 / 70 / 71 |\n51\t| `safe-export`     | `fathomdb doctor safe-export <out> [--manifest <path>]`                        | `doctor-export-*` = 0 / 66 / 71     |\n52\t| `verify-embedder` | `fathomdb doctor verify-embedder --identity <s> --dimension <n>`               | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65           |\n53\t| `trace`           | `fathomdb doctor trace --source-ref <id>`                                      | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n54\t| `dump-schema`     | `fathomdb doctor dump-schema`                                                  | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n55\t| `dump-row-counts` | `fathomdb doctor dump-row-counts`                                              | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n56\t| `dump-profile`    | `fathomdb doctor dump-profile`                                                 | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n57\t\n58\t`doctor-check-*` means the verb may use the exit-code class set `{0, 65, 70,\n59\t71}` depending on clean/findings/unrecoverable/lock-held outcome.\n60\t\n61\t## Recover root\n62\t\n63\t`recover` is the only lossy / non-bit-preserving root in 0.6.0.\n64\t\n65\t```text\n66\tfathomdb recover --accept-data-loss\n67\t  [--truncate-wal]\n68\t  [--rebuild-vec0]\n69\t  [--rebuild-projections]\n70\t  [--excise-source <id>]\n71\t  [--purge-logical-id <id>]\n72\t  [--restore-logical-id <id>]\n73\t```\n74\t\n75\tExit class: `recover-*` = 0 / 64 / 70 / 71.\n76\t\n77\t`--accept-data-loss` is declared on the `recover` parser only. `doctor` verbs\n78\treject it as unknown.\n79\t\n80\t`--rebuild-projections` is the canonical 0.6.0 regenerate workflow for failed\n81\tor stale projections. The docs may refer to \"regenerate\" as the workflow name,\n82\tbut there is no separate `fathomdb regenerate` command in 0.6.0.\n83\t\n84\t## Error to exit-code mapping\n85\t\n86\tThe CLI dispatcher translates engine error variants (and CLI-detected\n87\tpreconditions) to the exit-code classes above. This table binds each variant\n88\tto its class.\n89\t\n90\t| Source error variant                             | Exit code | Class         |\n91\t| ------------------------------------------------ | --------- | ------------- |\n92\t| (clean completion)                               | 0         | success       |\n93\t| recover sub-action gated by `--accept-data-loss` | 64        | data-loss-ack |\n94\t| `doctor check-integrity` findings non-empty      | 65        | findings      |\n95\t| `doctor safe-export` failed manifest/export step | 66        | artifact-fail |\n96\t| `EngineError::Storage`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |\n97\t| `EngineError::Projection`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n98\t| `EngineError::Vector`                            | 70        | unrecoverable |\n99\t| `EngineError::Embedder`                          | 70        | unrecoverable |\n100\t| `EngineError::Scheduler`                         | 70        | unrecoverable |\n101\t| `EngineError::OpStore`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |\n102\t| `EngineError::Overloaded`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n103\t| `EngineError::SchemaValidation`                  | 70        | unrecoverable |\n104\t| `EngineError::WriteValidation`                   | 70        | unrecoverable |\n105\t| `EngineError::EmbedderNotConfigured`             | 70        | unrecoverable |\n106\t| `EngineError::KindNotVectorIndexed`              | 70        | unrecoverable |\n107\t| `EngineError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}`     | 70        | unrecoverable |\n108\t| `EngineOpenError::DatabaseLocked{..}`            | 71        | lock-held     |\n109\t| `EngineError::Closing`                           | 71        | lock-held     |\n110\t| `EngineOpenError::Corruption(..)`                | 70        | unrecoverable |\n111\t| `EngineOpenError::IncompatibleSchemaVersion{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |\n112\t| `EngineOpenError::MigrationError{..}`            | 70        | unrecoverable |\n113\t| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderIdentityMismatch{..}`  | 70        | unrecoverable |\n114\t| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |\n115\t| `EngineOpenError::Io{..}`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n116\t\n117\t## JSON output wrapping\n118\t\n119\t`fathomdb-cli` owns top-level discriminator wrapping. The engine returns"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6045b345-74e5-4485-9471-2a1561990851","uuid":"c329ca3c-0ece-434b-abf2-84b6dcb5efd9","timestamp":"2026-05-15T23:42:41.095Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-10b-A-low-risk-seams-20260515T234104Z/dev/interfaces/cli.md","content":"| `64` | recovery completed only because lossy action was explicitly accepted | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n| `65` | doctor/verification surface found actionable non-clean state         | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n| `66` | export/materialization failure on an artifact-producing doctor verb  | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n| `70` | unrecoverable command failure                                        | this file                        |\n| `71` | lock-held or equivalent precondition-blocked outcome                 | this file + `design/bindings.md` |\n\n## Doctor verbs\n\n| Verb              | Synopsis                                                                       | Exit class                          |\n| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------- |\n| `check-integrity` | `fathomdb doctor check-integrity [--quick] [--full] [--round-trip] [--pretty]` | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65 / 70 / 71 |\n| `safe-export`     | `fathomdb doctor safe-export <out> [--manifest <path>]`                        | `doctor-export-*` = 0 / 66 / 71     |\n| `verify-embedder` | `fathomdb doctor verify-embedder --identity <s> --dimension <n>`               | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65           |\n| `trace`           | `fathomdb doctor trace --source-ref <id>`                                      | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n| `dump-schema`     | `fathomdb doctor dump-schema`                                                  | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n| `dump-row-counts` | `fathomdb doctor dump-row-counts`                                              | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n| `dump-profile`    | `fathomdb doctor dump-profile`                                                 | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n\n`doctor-check-*` means the verb may use the exit-code class set `{0, 65, 70,\n71}` depending on clean/findings/unrecoverable/lock-held outcome.\n\n## Recover root\n\n`recover` is the only lossy / non-bit-preserving root in 0.6.0.\n\n```text\nfathomdb recover --accept-data-loss\n  [--truncate-wal]\n  [--rebuild-vec0]\n  [--rebuild-projections]\n  [--excise-source <id>]\n  [--purge-logical-id <id>]\n  [--restore-logical-id <id>]\n```\n\nExit class: `recover-*` = 0 / 64 / 70 / 71.\n\n`--accept-data-loss` is declared on the `recover` parser only. `doctor` verbs\nreject it as unknown.\n\n`--rebuild-projections` is the canonical 0.6.0 regenerate workflow for failed\nor stale projections. The docs may refer to \"regenerate\" as the workflow name,\nbut there is no separate `fathomdb regenerate` command in 0.6.0.\n\n## Error to exit-code mapping\n\nThe CLI dispatcher translates engine error variants (and CLI-detected\npreconditions) to the exit-code classes above. This table binds each variant\nto its class.\n\n| Source error variant                             | Exit code | Class         |\n| ------------------------------------------------ | --------- | ------------- |\n| (clean completion)                               | 0         | success       |\n| recover sub-action gated by `--accept-data-loss` | 64        | data-loss-ack |\n| `doctor check-integrity` findings non-empty      | 65        | findings      |\n| `doctor safe-export` failed manifest/export step | 66        | artifact-fail |\n| `EngineError::Storage`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Projection`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Vector`                            | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Embedder`                          | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Scheduler`                         | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::OpStore`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Overloaded`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::SchemaValidation`                  | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::WriteValidation`                   | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::EmbedderNotConfigured`             | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::KindNotVectorIndexed`              | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}`     | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::DatabaseLocked{..}`            | 71        | lock-held     |\n| `EngineError::Closing`                           | 71        | lock-held     |\n| `EngineOpenError::Corruption(..)`                | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::IncompatibleSchemaVersion{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::MigrationError{..}`            | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderIdentityMismatch{..}`  | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::Io{..}`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n\n## JSON output wrapping\n\n`fathomdb-cli` owns top-level discriminator wrapping. The engine returns","numLines":80,"startLine":40,"totalLines":129}}}
